  "body": "### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nWe followed the documentation here ( https://quarkus.io/guides/rest-json#servlet-compatibility ) to obstain the remote address in a JAX-RS app from a `ContainerRequestFilter`. It certainly works in dev mode, but it doesn't inject in the same project compiled to native image. The `request` property is never injected (remains `null`). There isn't any failure logged about it either, it just doesn't get set for some reason.\r\n\r\n### How to Reproduce?\r\n\r\n```kt\r\n@Provider\r\n@PreMatching\r\nclass AuthenticationInterceptor : ContainerRequestFilter {\r\n\r\n    // Need to inject the RestEasy SPI HttpRequest to get remote address\r\n    // https://quarkus.io/guides/rest-json#servlet-compatibility\r\n    @Context\r\n    var request: org.jboss.resteasy.spi.HttpRequest? = null\r\n\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Output of `uname -a` or `ver`\r\n\r\nquay.io/quarkus/centos-quarkus-maven:21.0-java11\r\n\r\n### Output of `java -version`\r\n\r\nquay.io/quarkus/centos-quarkus-maven:21.0-java11\r\n\r\n### GraalVM version (if different from Java)\r\n\r\nquay.io/quarkus/centos-quarkus-maven:21.0-java11\r\n\r\n### Quarkus version or git rev\r\n\r\n1.13.2.Final\r\n\r\n### Build tool (ie. output of `mvnw --version` or `gradlew --version`)\r\n\r\n3.6.2\r\n\r\n",
